<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=alyssa201&buddyTimeStamp=20051219&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fprocess_buddy.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193059702&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Elizabeth</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Elizabeth lives at <a href='/home/?user=alyssa201'>5460 Glacier Road</a>, on the very top of King's Hill in Westridge.  Elizabeth has been a Millsberry resident since November 18, 2004.  She's certainly enjoyed her first year in town and looks forward to many more!<br><br>Elizabeth has quickly earned a reputation for her abilities on the soccer field.  Every afternoon, if the weather is good, Elizabeth heads straight for <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park/">Peabody Park</a> after class lets out at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/">Millsberry Academy</a>.  There, Elizabeth and her friends will usually play a full game of soccer, but sometimes they simply practice their penalty-kicking or dribbling and passing the ball.  Elizabeth first started playing when her science teacher taught the class about the connection between physics (Elizabeth's favorite subject) and soccer.  Elizabeth's curiosity got her out on the field, and she's been lacing up her cleats almost every day since!<br><br>Elizabeth's athleticism doesn't end with just soccer, however.  During the summer, you can often find her at a pool, racing through the water in her favorite green, light blue, and zebra bathing suit.  Elizabeth is also very generous with her free time, so she devotes quite a few hours in the summer to teaching younger children how to swim.<br><br>Elizabeth isn't just a star athlete, though.  She's also very expressive; in fact, her friends often jokingly tease Elizabeth about wearing her heart on her sleeve.  Elizabeth ended up deciding that the perfect use for her expressiveness was music!  It's always been one of her biggest passions, so Elizabeth combined her heartfelt lyrics with her favorite pop, techno, and rap beats to create a sound that is the perfect expression of who she is.  Her songs soon earned many fans, whose enthusiasm for Elizabeth's work has taken one of her mixes to the top of the Cinnamon Toast Crunch Top Ten chart!<br><br>Thank you for being a fine citizen, Elizabeth, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
